Wole Balogun, Ado-Ekiti As part of his restoration agenda, Governor Kayode Fayemi of Ekiti State will, on Monday, November 5, commence a tour of key project sites and infrastructure across the state, with a view to getting on- the- spot assessment of ongoing and abandoned projects in all the 16 local government areas of the state. According to a press release by the governor’s Chief Press Secretary (CPS), Yinka Oyebode, the governor will be accompanied on the week-long tour by top government functionaries and heads/ supervisors of relevant projects. READ ALSO: Amaechi rescues kidnap victim The project tour is a follow up to two weeks of briefings by heads of Ministries, Departments and agencies of government. 